Description: Heavily corroded fragment of copper alloy vessel, with a rim and a handle; the curve of the rim indicates that the vessel had a large diameter and a shape similar to the cooking pots.
Curator's comments: Provenance aacording to the Museum register
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.42, p.52, p.173, pl.15)
